##As a student staying in China, I'm afraid that I'm going to drop out of school

Vicechina  

Function description, different color vision

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The new crown has given 2020 a nightmarish start, with the virus spreading fast and everything happening fast. China is experiencing an unexpected disaster, and the world is facing a major threat. The International Health Organization has announced a "public health emergency. " Countries have closed down their ports and a large number of air routes have been suspended, national and even world level emergency, preservation decision-making are launched in a very short time.

On the morning of February 1, my flight from Singapore to Sydney was cancelled. On the afternoon of February 1, the Australian prime minister announced a 14-day restriction with immediate effect. As a college student in Sydney, the school can not go back.

In just two days my studies came to a halt.

My home in Guangdong, is now the country outside Hubei confirmed cases of the most provinces. At the moment, no school, in order to be forced to stay at home in order to prevent the epidemic, which I usually read work to go outside, the more boring the more people want to go out, it is not used to. Daily life is full of vigilance, mask wet towel hand sanitizer is a must, even if out, encounter people go around, take home express also have to open the door to the door.

At home, I no longer have to set the alarm clock for class and work, but my mother and I set the alarm clock for a mask every day. Guangzhou every night at 8:00 in the "Sui Kang" small program to reserve the next day's five masks, so we every day at 7:55 alarm clock, 7:59 began desperately press the "I want to make an appointment to buy" , today up to 10 days to try, it never worked once.

I miss the days when there were lights and people's smoke in Guangzhou

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The outbreak and spread of the new crown reminded me of the word "natural disaster" again and again. Of course, we can also regard this epidemic as a "man-made disaster" caused by eating wild game, but for the vast majority of people, i think it was a disaster that fell from the sky for no reason. Especially for the sick, the people in the center of the epidemic area, this is a life-threatening disaster.

As of yesterday (February 9 at 1400 hours) , 37,262 people across the country had been diagnosed with a new crown. That may not seem like a large proportion of the population of 1.4 billion, but I always recall the phrase: for the individuals and families who are hit, that's a 100% .

If we put "luck" and "misfortune" at the two ends of a scale, the whole world is inclined to "misfortune" , and in this "great misfortune" , I am actually lucky: currently healthy, relatives and friends are safe. In this time of massive shutdown, I can complain about the daily pain of a house, home boring, all of which is not "lucky" ?

Of course. Is there anyone I know who's luckier than me? Yes, there is.

Xiao Xin, a student of mine in Sydney, was waiting in line at the security checkpoint after checking her luggage when the restrictions were announced. This is a flight from Qingdao to Seoul to Sydney, suddenly there is an official closure, but this flight has not been cancelled.

So, are we going or not?

"It was quite scary, because I was still at the security gate and didn't get in, so I thought I'd just let it go, " Shin said.

The "immediate effect" Australian ban leaves a blind spot: The time announced is 2 pm, but what about the people on the plane at that time? The one-size-fits-all policy of isolation, repatriation, and smooth entry has left many Chinese students between borders, caught in a great deal of anxiety and uncertainty.

The announcement of the ban also triggered a small letter's circle of friends, a large number of time and true or false information, so that small letter has been wavering in the heart.

"There are a lot of people who are analyzing this policy, and they're not analyzing it right, but they're saying it with absolute certainty. "

In the end, she chose to walk through security to get on the plane. Fortunately, all the way smooth, transfer Seoul staff to help confirm, after landing in Sydney is all the way card, clearance, luggage, declaration and no unusual.

Astrid is another friend who seems to me to be relatively "lucky" . She was a student in my dorm in Sydney and did not return home for the Spring Festival in her hometown of Shiyan, Hubei Province (as of 1400 hours on February 9,467 cases had been confirmed, none had died and 40 had been cured) .

"I was supposed to be on a 9:30 flight on New Year's Eve, but my dad texted me this morning, saying the death toll was 17 and it was best not to return. Before that, I had been struggling for a day or two, wondering whether to go back to China or not? Where is it safe to fly?"She told me.

In order to get home, Astrid had already changed her schedule several times, moving all the high-speed trains from Wuhan to Zhengzhou.

But seeing the epidemic getting worse, she finally made the decision to cancel her plane ticket three hours before the flight, becoming a "left-behind child" in Sydney for the New Year and "fortunate" not to have to participate in the ordeal.

New Year's dinner, Astrid

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
But even so, life is not easy. This is perhaps the biggest peacetime pause we've ever experienced in our twenties.

"Do you regret not going home? " I asked Astrid.

On the other end of the phone, she seemed to have a sentence about to burst out, but it was swallowed back.

She thought about it, calmly said: "The comprehensive words, did not say that is lucky or the regret, I thought that my choice at present is correct. ". I have a job here, the 24th of Wuhan closed, the 25th of my home closed, then I can not come back. The second was that I would inevitably meet some infected people on my way back to Hubei during the Spring Festival. Even if I was young and my resistance was good and I hadn't been infected, then I might have taken the virus home with me. That's why I decided to cancel the plane ticket at that time. I thought it was right."

That's the right, rational answer.

"But if they are infected and need me to take care of them, then I must leave them and go back, " she added.

On the other side of the world, it's hard to watch your home town become a plague zone.

The first thing she does every day when she wakes up is to see how many new cases have been added to the Shiyan, what news is there, and watch it with sadness. Spring Festival is a day of Reunion, even if the Spring Festival under the disaster can not be celebrated together, could have been, but also hope to have a hard shoulder.

But in the end, the distance to the eye, overseas "stay" more can only be a spectator: heard which family members have a slight cold, which friends today a bit burned, which hospital and no beds can not go. What you can do, however, is to look at your phone more and send more messages.

"I send them [ their families ] wechat every day, especially after the 23rd closure. News, Useful News, viral knowledge, how to protect yourself, how to eat, how to wear a mask, how to boost your immune system... I have a circle of friends that is only visible to my family, and I found that for three or four days I was so crazy that when I saw something useful, I uploaded a dozen messages a day,"Astrid said.

Family Chats. Photo from Astrid

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
It was a university holiday in Australia, and Astrid was working in a business student apartment called Urbanest. There are a lot of Chinese students living there. February is the beginning of the school year. It was supposed to be the peak time for students to move in, but now it is deserted because of the new Tiara and closure.

"there was a check-in on the morning of February 1, arrived at 10 a.m. , and the closure and quarantine policy was in the afternoon. We told him you needed to be quarantined for 14 days and he said 'ok' . "

Such an understatement of the "good" , also do not know what kind of mood is hidden behind.

Tian Tian is another friend of my dormitory. He had the honor to fly back to Sydney from Beijing before the Australian Customs. But now he is being asked by the dormitory to isolate himself. He can not go out for 14 days. He can not contact other people in the dormitory, daily necessities and food are all ordered from the Internet, take-out can only use the back door of the dormitory.

"What do you do every day? " I asked her.

"read extra-curricular books and watch videos with family and friends. "

"Do you feel all right? "

"It's quite depressing, but sometimes it's quite quiet. I'm a Buddhist, and we chant the heart sutras and prayers every day, so I think that supports me. "

The most recent book to read every day, the picture from every day

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Australian spider bug big summer, today she suddenly sent a message that found a spider in the bathroom, but can not get help, I can only remote, seems to be very inattentive and she said "careful. ".

Those who are stuck at home envy those abroad who can go to school as usual and those who are stuck abroad are accompanied by their families. We all like to compare. We all feel better looking at someone else's.

But he said to me every day, "I always think that there is no perfect place in the world, or every place is perfect, freedom for me is not where, have to find in their own hearts. There are advantages at home and abroad. Here, with the company of your family and everything you know, you rely on independence and discretion."

Halfway through this article, I received an email from my college dorm room to the effect that I had 48 hours to decide whether or not to cancel my reservation for the new semester because of the new crown, if you don't decide, a $1,000 refund will be paid in three days, and a semester's rent will be gone in 10 days.

Realizing that I was "living on the street, " I replied to an e-mail with no hope. "There's no way to know if we can postpone this. " I didn't expect to hear from them soon. They said they would consider my offer, and that they would be in touch with me ASAP.

I hope this ASAP is a good sign, this gloomy day, please hurry up and shine.
